ontroversies%20involving%20Zhong.%20It%20was%20reported%20that%20Ms%20Zhong%20accepted%20bribes%20and%20used%20her%20position%20to%20ensure%20that%20companies%20she%20favoured%20received%20lucrative%20contracts%2C%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20government%20investment.%20This%20included%20approving%20the%20development%20of%20land%20in%20a%20high-tech%20industrial%20estate%20for%20a%20businessman%20who%20had%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%2C%20a%20private%20business%20owner%20claimed%20that%20Ms%20Zhong%20would%20neglect%20companies%20without%20personal%20ties%20to%20her.%20The%20documentary%20also%20revealed%20that%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Guizhou%20Provincial%20Discipline%20Inspection%20and%20Supervision%20Committee%20announced%20that%20Ms%20Zhong%20was%20suspected%20of%20serious%20disciplinary%20and%20legal%20violations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%2052-year-old%20has%20also%20been%20accused%20of%20engaging%20in%20affairs%20with%2058%20male%20subordinates.%20Some%20reportedly%20chose%20to%20be%20her%20lover%20due%20to%20the%20advantages%20she%20offered%2C%20while%20others%20did%20so%20reluctantly%20as%20they%20feared%20her%20authority.%20Ms%20Zhong%20allegedly%20spent%20time%20with%20her%20lovers%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20working%20overtime%20and%20going%20on%20business%20trips.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthai-woman-64-rescued-after-being-in-pythons-grip-for-2-hours-6606269%5C%22%3EThai%20Woman%2C%2064%2C%20Rescued%20After%20Being%20In%20Python's%20Grip%20For%202%20Hours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Zhong%20was%20arrested%20in%20April%202023.%20In%20September%2C%20she%20was%20removed%20from%20office%20and%20expelled%20from%20the%20CPC.%20She%20also%20lost%20her%20position%20in%20the%20National%20People's%20Congress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20documentary%2C%20Ms%