%20around%202018%2C%20its%20lead%20began%20to%20crumble%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20series%20of%20missteps.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsmc-power-players-14-execs-leading-worlds-biggest-chipmaker-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETSMC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20upstart%20from%20Taiwan%2C%20steadily%20gained%20and%20is%20now%20unquestionably%20the%20best%20chipmaker%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg's%20veteran%20chip%20reporter%20Ian%20King%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2018-11-28%2Fintel-s-chipmaking-throne-is-challenged-by-a-taiwanese-upstart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20about%20this%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%202018.%20Since%20then%2C%20Intel%20has%20plummeted%20and%20TSMC%20has%20soared.%20Intel%20is%20now%20worth%20less%20than%20%24100%20billion.%20It%20doesn't%20even%20crack%20the%20top%20150%20companies%20based%20on%20this%20measure.%20TSMC%20is%20worth%20almost%20%241%20trillion%20these%20days%2C%20putting%20it%20in%20the%20top%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224433195c-e4af-462a-9ced-7b54c27e82a4%5C%22%3EWhy%20countries%20must%20have%20fabs%20now%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20astounding%20fall%20from%20grace%20for%20Intel%2C%20and%20a%20huge%20strategic%20and%20geopolitical%20problem%20for%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20best%20chips%2C%20you%20have%20to%20go%20to%20Taiwan%20to%20get%20them%20made.%20Or%20maybe%20South%20Korea%2C%20where%20Samsung%20has%20built%20an%20impressive%20so-called%20foundry%20business%20making%20semiconductors%20for%20other%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20famous%20%26quot%3Bchipmakers%26quot%3B%20we%20think%20of%20in%20the%20US%20today%20%3Cem%3Edon't%20actually%20make%20chips%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Nvidia%2C%20Qualcomm%2C%20AMD%2C%20and%20all%20the%20others%20design%20chips%2C%20then%20they%20usually%20have%20TSMC%20manufacture%20them.%20Apple%20and%20a%20host%20of%20other%20big%20tech%20giants%20also%20have%20TSMC%20make%20the%20chips%20they%20design%20in-house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20actually%20producing%20these%20complex%20products%20at%20massive%20scale%2C%20with%20no%20tiny%20imperfections%2C%20is%20incredibly%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20China%20invades%20Taiwan%2C%20or%20somehow%20exerts%20much%20more%20control%20over%20this%20island%20nation%2C%20this%20will%20be%20a%20disaster%20for%20the%20US%2C%20and%20Europe%20for%20that%20matter.%20No%20more%20fast%20iPhones%20for%20a%20while.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-taiwan-tsmc-jensen-huang-china-disruption-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENvidia%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20have%20to%20look%20elsewhere%20to%20have%20its%20GPUs%20made.%20AI%20progress%20could%20stall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%2C%20today%2C%20%26quot%3Breal%20countries%20have%20fabs%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20better%20catch-phrase.%20Chips%20power%20the%20modern%20economy.%20If%20you%20have%20to%20get%20these%20components%20overseas%2C%20you're%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283c00bc8-d296-4cf5-a23e-c8c8e45af39c%5C%22%3EQualcomm%20won't%20fix%20Intel's%20worrying%20decline%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20why%20the%20decline%20of%20Intel%20is%20so%20worrying.%20It's%20the%20only%20US%20company%20that%20knows%20how%20to%20manufacture%20powerful%20chips%20at%20scale.%20(Globalfoundries%20also%20makes%20semiconductors%2C%20but%20not%20the%20cutting-edge%20ones).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WSJ%20reported%20on%20Friday%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fqualcomm-intel-acquisition-chips-semiconductors-tsmc-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EQualcomm%20approached%20Intel%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20about%20a%20deal.%20That%20followed%20a%20report%20from%20Reuters%20two%20weeks%20ago%20that%20Qualcomm%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fqualcomm-has-explored-acquiring-pieces-intel-chip-design-business-sources-say-2024-09-06%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsidering%20buying%20pieces%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Intel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20deal%20materializes%2C%20it%20won't%20solve%20America's%20chipmaking%20problem.%20One%20analyst%20called%20a%20potential%20tie-up%20%26quot%3Bodd.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQualcomm%20is%20probably%20not%20interested%20in%20Intel's%20manufacturing%20operations.%20As%20Reuters%20reported%2C%20it's%20keen%20on%20some%20of%20the%20chip-design%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%202%20main%20businesses.%20In%20one%2C%20it%20designs%20semiconductors%20for%20PCs%2C%20data%20center%20servers%20and%20other%20uses.%20The%20other%20part%20manufactures%20these%20designs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20Intel's%20design%20and%20manufacturing%20operations%20were%20tightly%20integrated.%20This%20worked%20great%20for%20ages.%20The%20company%20could%20set%20up%20its%20factories%20to%20the%20exact%20specifications%20of%20its%20in-house%20chip%20designers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20the%20world%20began%20to%20move%20to%20a%20different%20approach%2C%20pioneered%20by%20TSMC.%20Instead%20of%20both%20designing%20and%20making%20your%20own%20chips%2C%20why%20not%20just%20run%20the%20fabs%20and%20make%20chips%20for%20other%20companies%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20when%20TSMC%20got%20going%2C%20this%20idea%20was%20laughed%20at.%20(Hence%20the%20sexist%20comment%20from%20AMD's%20Sanders%20about%20real%20men%20owning%20fabs).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20TSMC's%20approach%20gradually%20caught%20on%2C%20helped%20by%20Intel%20mistakes%20and%20the%20march%20of%20modern%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20one%20happened%20when%20Intel%20missed%20out%20on%20making%20chips%20for%20the%20iPhone%20when%20that%20revolutionary%20device%20was%20first%20coming%20out.%20Apple%20ended%20up%20going%20with%20TSMC.%20Qualcomm%20is%20a%20huge%20smartphone%20chip%20designer%20too%2C%20and%20it%20has%20TSMC%20make%20most%20of%20these%20components.%20Other%20chip%20designers%2C%20including%20AMD%2C%20also%20began%20turning%20to%20TSMC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20gave%20TSMC%20the%20huge%2C%20diverse%20manufacturing%20volumes%20it%20needed%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20make%20chips%20better%20than%20anyone%20else.%20Ian%20King's%202018%20article%20describes%20this%20virtuous%20feedback%20loop%20well%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20billions%20of%20transistors%20on%20chips%2C%20a%20problem%20with%20a%20small%20number%20of%20those%20tiny%20switches%20can%20render%20the%20whole%20component%20useless.%20Production%20runs%20can%20take%20up%20to%20six%20months%20and%20involve%20hundreds%20of%20steps%20requiring%20maniacal%20attention%20to%20detail.%20Each%20time%20there's%20a%20mistake%2C%20the%20factory%20operator%20has%20a%20chance%20to%20make%20tweaks%20and%20try%20a%20new%20approach.%20If%20the%20change%20works%2C%20that%20information%20is%20retained%20to%20try%20on%20the%20next%20challenge.%20The%20more%20production%20runs%2C%20the%20better.%20And%20TSMC%20has%20the%20most%20nowadays.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20TSMC%20was%20learning%20from%20this%20wide%20variety%20of%20huge%20customers%2C%20Intel's%20manufacturing%20operation%20was%20stuck%20with%20just%20one%20customer%3A%20Itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20smartphone%20chips%20became%20the%20biggest%20game%20in%20town%2C%20Intel%20just%20didn't%20have%20the%20volume%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20TSMC%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20race.%20AI%20has%20made%20this%20situation%20worse.%20Nvidia%20leads%20here%20by%20a%20mile%2C%20and%20TSMC%20manufactures%20its%20GPUs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22564b92fa-9e3c-4629-a190-2efc5f73990c%5C%22%3EA%20stubborn%20manufacturing%20miasma%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELifting%20the%20manufacturing%20miasma%20around%20Intel%20will%20be%20an%20expensive%2C%20risky%2C%20and%20complex%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel%20has%20even%20begun%20paying%20TSMC%20to%20make%20some%20of%20its%20chips.%20With%20that%20as%20a%20starting%20point%2C%20there's%20a%20very%20long%20way%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20company%20took%20a%20major%20step%20recently%20when%20it%20separated%20its%20Foundry%20business%20from%20its%20chip-design%20business.%20This%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20outside%20customers%20to%20trust%20Intel%20to%20make%20their%20chips%20without%20competing%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20challenge%20is%20the%20biggest%3A%20%3Cem%3EActually%20being%20really%20good%20at%20making%20chips%20again%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel's%20Foundry%20business%20won't%20really%20be%20able%20to%20challenge%20TSMC%20until%20it%20gets%20several%20big%20customers.%20Again%2C%20to%20get%20good%20at%20chip%20manufacturing%20you%20need%20huge%2C%20diverse%20volumes%20so%20you%20can%20spot%20defects%2C%20fix%20processes%2C%20and%20feed%20that%20knowledge%20back%20into%20your%20fabs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20chicken-and-egg%20situation.%20Without%20big%20volumes%2C%20outside%20customers%20will%20be%20wary%20of%20having%20Intel%20make%20their%20precious%20chip%20designs.%20But%20without%20customers%2C%20Intel%20can't%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22404cc2a8-c10e-43b4-a322-b06714d18898%5C%22%3EDoes%20everyone%20love%20Raimondo%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20break%20this%20deadlock%3A%20Get%20the%20US%20government%20to%20coax%20other%20companies%20to%20use%20Intel's%20fabs.%20This%20is%20exactly%20what's%20happening%20now%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2024%2F09%2F12%2Fintel-gets-boost-from-raimondo-effort-to-spur-us-chip-production.html%3Fs%3D31%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20CNBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommerce%20Secretary%20Gina%20Raimondo%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20urge%20shareholders%20in%20companies%20such%20as%20Nvidia%20and%20Apple%20to%20recognize%20the%20economic%20benefits%20of%20having%20a%20US%20foundry%20that%20can%20produce%20AI%20chips%2C%20CNBC%20reported%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%204%20days%20later%2C%20Intel%20announced%20a%20partnership%20where%20it%20will%20make%20an%20AI%20chip%20for%20Amazon%20Web%20Services.%20Intel%20stock%20jumped%20on%20the%20news%20because%20AWS%20is%20the%20largest%20cloud%20provider%20and%20it%20designs%20a%20boatload%20of%20chips%20for%20use%20in%20its%20huge%20data%20centers.%20This%20is%20the%20type%20of%20volume%20Intel%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ea79bb3-2393-462a-a292-8ee9d215d571%5C%22%3E18A%20hopes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20technology%20side%2C%20Intel%20has%20a%20new%20process%20node%2C%20called%2018A.%20This%20is%20a%20set%20of%20chip%20design%20rules%20and%20an%20accompanying%20manufacturing%20system.%20If%20everything%20goes%20well%20in%20come%20years%2C%20this%20could%20make%20Intel%20more%20competitive%20with%20TSMC's%20leading%20nodes%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AWS%20partnership%20is%20based%20on%20this%2018A%20technology%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20said%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20it%20will%20have%20an%20in-house%20chip%20made%20on%20this%20process%20node%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIntel's%20Foundry%20business%20just%20needs%20way%20more%20of%20these%20customers.%20And%20the%2018A%20technology%20must%20work%20really%20well%20for%20that%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B18A%20had%20better%20be%20spectacular%20as%20they%20are%20betting%20the%20company%20on%20its%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20Bernstein%20chip%20analyst%20Stacy%20Rasgon%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note%20to%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22227c7e91-ea62-4e83-bba6-deed17b6cebd%5C%22%3EWould%20a%20split%20work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Qualcomm%20is%20unlikely%20to%20want%20to%20acquire%20this%20part%20of%20Intel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20raises%20the%20specter%20of%20Intel%20being%20broken%20up%2C%20something%20that's%20been%20speculated%20in%20recent%20months.%20Reuters%20said%20Qualcomm%20is%20interested%20in%20some%20of%20the%20chip-design%20operations%2C%20while%20the%20WSJ%20reported%20on%20Friday%20that%20Qualcomm%20would%20likely%20sell%20some%20parts%20of%20Intel%20to%20other%20buyers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20would%20Intel's%20Foundry%20business%20perform%20as%20a%20separate%20company%2C%20split%20off%20from%20the%20design%20parts%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20here%2C%20again%2C%20is%20all%20about%20volume.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20Intel's%20Foundry%20business%20needs%20the%20manufacturing%20volume%20it%20gets%20from%20the%20company's%20own%20chip%20designs.%20Without%20that%2C%20it%20would%20have%20very%20little%20manufacturing%20to%20learn%20from.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20don't%20see%20how%20it%20could%20really%20be%20done%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Rasgon%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20in%20early%20September.%20%26quot%3BThe%20manufacturing%20arm%20cannot%20stand%20on%20its%20own%20right%20now%20given%20heavy%20losses%20and%20lack%20of%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20split%20really%20only%20makes%20sense%20once%20it%20attracts%20a%20substantial%20third%20party%20business%20which%20seems%20years%20away%20(if%20ever)%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-qualcomm-odd-couple-wont-solve-us-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726882118000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ee04b3d17aa3c7b2b4cd65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-qualcomm-odd-couple-wont-solve-us-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Intel's%20manufacturing%20struggles%20continue%2C%20any%20potential%20deal%20with%20Qualcomm%20won't%20fix%20America's%20chipmaking%20dilemma.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Alistair%20Barr)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fintel-qualcomm-odd-couple-wont-solve-us-chipmaking-woes-2024-9%