t%20there%20was%20once%20an%20island%20to%20the%20west%20of%20the%20fossil%20site%20where%20the%20bird%20may%20have%20visited.%20It%20started%20to%20change%20Bischoff's%20ideas%20on%20California's%20geology%20during%20the%20Miocene%20epoch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weight%20of%20debris%20from%20volcanic%20eruptions%20would%20have%20collapsed%20the%20island's%20slopes%2C%20creating%20a%20canyon%20where%20the%20fossils%20accumulated.%20Tectonic%20activity%20eventually%20helped%20the%20beds%20reemerge%20closer%20to%20the%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20might%20have%20been%20other%20pieces%20of%20land%20in%20the%20area%2C%20too.%20Geologists%20are%20studying%20how%20and%20where%20channel%20islands%20might%20have%20formed%20and%20sunk%20off%20the%20state's%20coast%20during%20this%20epoch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBischoff%20will%20get%20to%20name%20the%20extinct%20island.%20He%20was%20leaning%20toward%20San%20Pedro%20Island%20until%20his%20wife%20suggested%20he%20name%20it%20after%20her%3A%20Shelley%20Island.%20He's%20been%20polling%20people.%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20asking%20which%20people%20prefer%2C%20and%20she%20is%20winning%20by%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20San%20Pedro%20students%20especially%20side%20with%20her!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20oldest%20fossils%20from%208.9%20million%20years%20ago%20included%20megalodon%20teeth.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223780%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20rows%20of%20fossil%20shark%20teeth%20including%20megalodon%20teeth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66edaec8d17aa3c7b2b4a5a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222086%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMegalodon%20sharks%20were%20massive%2C%20and%20so%20were%20their%20teeth.%20Those%20shown%20here%20belonged%20to%20juveniles.%3Cp%3EEnvicom%20Corporation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20school%20wasn't%20done%20giving%20up%20its%20secrets.%20Older%20fossils%20lay%20even%20deeper%20beneath%20the%20bone%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%208.9-million-year-old%20rocks%20included%20fossilized%20bones%20of%20fish%20and%20marine%20mammals.%20Experts%20also%20found%20teeth%20from%20juvenile%20megalodons%20and%20other%20smaller%20sharks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-megalodon-sharks-got-so-big-what-they-ate-research-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMegalodons%20were%20enormous%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhm.ac.uk%2Fdiscover%2Fmegalodon--the-truth-about-the-largest-shark-that-ever-lived.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etimes%3C%2Fa%3E%20longer%20than%20a%20great%20white.%20An%20adult%20megalodon's%20teeth%20could%20grow%20as%20large%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fanimal%2Fmegalodon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%3C%2Fa%3E%207%20inches.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20megalodon%20shark%20was%20the%20apex%20predator%20in%20the%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20Bischoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20other%20fish%20swam%20alongside%20these%20giant%20hunters.%20The%20bone%20beds%20also%20included%20an%20extinct%20saber-tooth%20salmon.%20The%20unusual-looking%20fish%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.uoregon.edu%2Fsaber-no-more-giant-prehistoric-salmon-had-spike-teeth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%3C%2Fa%3E%20large%2C%20protruding%20teeth%2C%20had%20never%20been%20found%20in%20Southern%20California%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EStudents%20will%20help%20discover%20some%20of%20the%20fossils'%20secrets.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20child%20and%20man%20look%20at%20a%20fossil%20positioned%20under%20a%20camera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ec9dd6ce3009a0fac7dfef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223173%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWayne%20Bischoff%20helps%20student%20Decker%20Cullen%20look%20at%20a%20piece%20of%20coprolite%20using%20a%20camera.%3Cp%3EEnvicom%20Corporation%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20megalodon%20teeth%2C%20the%20oldest%20bone%20bed%20also%20contained%20lots%20of%20coprolites%2C%20fossilized%20poop%20full%20of%20fish%20bones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fossilized%20waste%20can%20help%20researchers%20learn%20exactly%20which%20animals%20were%20predators%20and%20prey.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20what's%20so%20fun%20about%20paleontology%2C%26quot%3B%20Hendy%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20detective%20work%2C%20so%20this%20is%20the%20classic%20whodunit.%20Who%20was%20eating%20who%20or%20being%20eaten%20by%20whom%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEighth-grader%20Decker%20Cullen%20got%20hands-on%20experience%20with%20the%20coprolite%20at%20Envicom%20Corporation%20as%20part%20of%20a%20school%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20SPHS%20students%20will%20soon%20get%20even%20more%20involved%20with%20the%20fossils%20that%20were%20once%20beneath%20their%20feet.%20They'll%20work%20on%20murals%2C%20publications%2C%20and%20research%20projects%2C%20Bischoff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Natural%20History%20Museum%2C%20Hendy%20has%20had%20kids%20sort%20some%20of%20the%20120%2C000-year-old%20shells.%20%26quot%3BThe%20kids%20love%20it%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20very%2C%20very%20easy%20sort%20of%20pathway%20into%20doing%20some%20real%20paleontology%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20SPHS%20site%20is%20one-of-a-kind%2C%20and%20there's%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20learn%20from%20it.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20wearing%20masks%20sort%20through%20fossil%20shells%20on%20a%20white%20table%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ec9f0cd17aa3c7b2b462e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENatural%20History%20Museum%20workers%20sort%20through%20fossils%20from%20the%20SPHS%20site.%3Cp%3EEnvicom%20Corporation%3C%